-- Nomura Hires JPMorgan’s Foster for Currency Trading in London
-- B y   E m m a   C h a r l t o n
-- 2012-03-27T14:45:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-27/nomura-hires-jpmorgan-s-foster-for-currency-trading-in-london.html
Nomura International Plc said
Antony Foster has joined its  London  office as the head of Group
of 10 spot trading for Europe,  Middle East  and Africa.  “Antony brings to the firm 14 years of experience in FX
trading, with a focus on G10 currencies,” the company said
today in a press release. “He joins from JPMorgan, where he
rose through the ranks after joining its graduate program in
1997 to become its Head of G10 FX Spot Trading.”  Foster will report to the co-heads of Europe, Middle East
and Africa foreign-exchange trading, Nigel Khakoo and Charlie Lovett-Turner and New York-based Brent Donnelly, global head of
G10 spot trading, according to Nomura’s press release.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emma Charlton in London at 
